<br>
nae, that is not true. You will not need a new database entry for each possible combination. You work your way around it user better parsing and storing some of that data in the character_profile table they would have for each character. <br>
<br>
Sim they screwed us on the not being able to dye armor...there are a few ways I can think of getting around it. Apart from that I know all the different breatplate look the same....(just a different color)...is there any graphic difference between an indo | vindicaiton | eradication | dyed crafted bp ? nope..not really...what is stopping them from allowing you to dye the bp of erradicaion? Only their coding. BUT assuming that you different bps DID have different graphics...then you could just force standard type of graphic for the colors...<br>
<br>
but off topic....short answer is...there is no need for a database entry for every possible combination of such a system. However if they designed their Database poorly then it would require work to get it to work efficiently.<br>
