<br>
It's not that their DB was designed poorly - it was designed just fine *for the task it was meant to implement*.  You can always design something more generically, true, but you sacrifice performance to do so.  I'd rather have EQ running smoothly than give people a random chance at getting +36hp instead of +35.<br>
