<br>
Instead of camping till the sword drops once, they'll sit there and camp, throwing away the lower versions of the sword, until the best version drops.  Perhaps they'll camp until they get &quot;any&quot; of the versions then leave, but rest ashured they're not done with that camp yet, and will return again and again until they get the one they really wanted.<br>
<br>
If anything, the way that mobs and spawn times are setup in this game has tought me, is that people will sit there and camp &quot;whatever&quot; for as long as it takes no matter what.  There will &quot;always&quot; be &quot;someone&quot; who will do this, blocking out spawns from the majority, in what ever game you play.<br>
<br>
A change like this would keep areas perma camped.  Or, we could just leave it alone and let the already working system work...  where they have to travel about Norrath to find the weapons they want off varied level of difficulty mobs.<br>
<br>
What you suggest is already in place (sort of)...  only instead of the same name with different stats, we have a different name for each item (which all have different stats).  Why have a sword that could be 9-12 damage 19-24 delay, when we have a 9/19 lammy dropping over there and a 12/24 CSS dropping over there, and all of the many items with stats in between dropping all over other places? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utenaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenaman</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/02 11:28:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22350.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: randomise the stats on items?</span><hr size=1> this would be utterly impossible to have as far as EQ goes.<br>
