The thing with that is all the items are 'better' or 'worse' what im saying is sometime you might get a 10/23 lammy another time a 11/18, another time a 8/19... etc <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzrekkanklestabber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zrekk Anklestabber</A> at: 2/20/02 7:50:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzrekkanklestabber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zrekk Anklestabber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/20/02 7:49:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22350.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Err</span><hr size=1> Sorry for replying to my own thread, but after rereading all fo this, i feel i must =b<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In medievia, a Popular MUD, I will try and Cite a good example.<br>
<br>
Gryphon claws were like ~6+Hit Roll, +30 to mana on average.(Im guessing, its been a WHILE)<br>
<br>
One time i got a No/Low Hitroll one with +48 mana.. It was nifty. It was a totally different version than say +12 hitroll +20 mana. and then you might get the ultra rare +12 +40, or even max stats combo, but this was very rare.<br>
<br>
Low end tweaks of items served as good noobie gifts, and high end versions served as higher-end gear. <br>
<br>
<br>
The stats dont just get 'better' or 'worse', they Get Different! What if you had a piece of &lt;insert clicky armor here&gt; that cast at a better resist rate but had less ac? Would you possibly find different uses for each? Sure!<br>
<br>
People camping 'midrange' items might get a shot at a really nice thing that could be traded off to someone a bit higher, or kept as a nice item for quite some time.<br>
<br>
With item tweaking you could have items drop more freely because not everything would be 'uber'<br>
<br>
In fact, weapons also were tweaked. A REALLY GOOD say, Short sword of flame, or 14d4 sword with say an extra d4 or 14d5 on it was something that was extremely rare and prized.<br>
<br>
<br>
Granted, full item looting helped keep stuff flowing<br>
<br>
As for the genious who posted earlier...<br>
&quot;So instead of asking Verant to create thousands of new items, you're asking them to add several fields of at least 1 byte apiece to each of *millions* of pieces of equipment in players' inventories? Yeah, that's likely&quot;<br>
<br>
No, the Item DB would contain baseline stats. You would put a value in the same place that the instance of the item is stored, probably only needing a byte or so.<br>
